				<title>New Horizon Internet JSC Company  - Data Center Engineer position</title>
				<description><![CDATA[ <b>Position</b>: Data Center Engineer

The Data Center Engineer plays a key role in maintaining a high availability service and supporting key objectives related to the data center.  Working schedule: 8-hour shifts with 2 working days/2 vacation days.

<b>Main responsibilities</b>

-         Monitor remstats/zabbix and inform the remote team about problems occured;

-         Replace faulted HDDs and other components;

-         Connect/Disconnect cables according to remote team's instructions;

-         Install new hardware into racks ind DC, help Gensys;

-         Operational contacts and functions with hardware vendors/suppliers and data centers;

-         (maybe) do initial OS install to new servers.

<b> Requirements</b>

-         Basic knowledge of Unix/Linux OS

-         Basic knowledge of networking & network devices (router, switch)

-         Good knowledge of PC\x86 hardware, HP Server hardware & DCâ€™s rack equipment

-         Hand-on experience in networking (or DC) cabling.

-         Good written English/ Good oral English will be a great advantage.

-         Self-motivation and ability to work with minimal supervision

-         Able to work closely with peers and remote teams on projects

Please send CV and cover letter to son.le@wada-co.vn]]></description>
